No Pitches | Only Passion

Find Out More

What is Wichitalks?

Wichitalks brings together the passionate individuals, high performers, and creative minds in our community to present on what drives them and provides a glimpse into the greater Wichita identity. At each event, 10 individuals present in a rapid fire environment, one after the next. With only 20 slides, each auto-advancing every 15 seconds, presentations are brief, fun, insightful, and passionately delivered. Wichitalks is an evening of eclectic presentations, inciting ideas and creative collisions that wouldn’t have otherwise happened. Absolutely no pitches are allowed. Presenters are individuals in Wichita who have a passion to share. They may be business owners, volunteers, or life-hackers. The goal is to teach something of social value and to spread ideas.

So, if you'd like to learn more about your city, Wichitalks is a great place to start.

We hope to see you there.

How does it work?

The Guidelines

20 Slides

Each speaker must have 20 slides.

15 Second Auto-Advance

Each slide auto-advances after 15 seconds to keep the talk moving.

No Pitches Allowed

Speakers are here to teach and share ideas, but with no strings attached.

#ilovewichita

Presenters are the everyday, passionate individuals that are defining Wichita.
